 your prompt action in helping make reserve items available to your colleagues placing items on reserve please provide adequate time to process lists while some items may already be in the library others may need to be recalled or purchased before each quarter a letter calling for reserve items is sent to faculty along with a list of items placed previously on reserve to expedite requests please amend the old list and provide complete bibliographic citations for new items before returning the list to swain you may need to obtain copyright clearance for photocopies before we can place them on reserve for you contact blandine clausing bclaus stanford edu for more information or assistance chemistry and chemical engineering back stanford university stanford california 94305 650 725 1064 terms of use copyright complaints
